Grosphus is doubtless the person whom Horace commends to Iccius in Epp. 1. 12. 22-24 :—

‘Utere Pompeio Grospho et, si quid petet, ultro defer3 nil Grosphus nisi verum orabit et aequum. vilis amicorum est annona bonis ubi quid deest?

We gather from this Ode that he was a man of wealth, and, from both Ode and Epistle, that his property was in Sicily.
